message.name: Heartbeat
message.description: The Heartbeat monitors the status of the communication link and identifies when the last of a string of messages was not received.

message.name: TestRequest
message.description: The test request message forces a heartbeat from the opposing application.

message.name: ResendRequest
message.description: The resend request is sent by the receiving application to initiate the retransmission of messages. This function is utilized if a sequence number gap is detected, if the receiving application lost a message, or as a function of the initialization process.

message.name: Reject
message.description: The reject message should be issued when a message is received but cannot be properly processed due to a session-level rule violation.

message.name: SequenceReset
message.description: The sequence reset message is used by the sending application to reset the incoming sequence number on the opposing side.

message.name: Logout
message.description: The logout message initiates or confirms the termination of a FIX session.

message.name: IOI
message.description: Indication of interest messages are used to market merchandise which the broker is buying or selling in either a proprietary or agency capacity.

message.name: Advertisement
message.description: Advertisement messages are used to announce completed transactions.

message.name: ExecutionReport
message.description: The execution report message is used to: 1. Confirm the receipt of an order 2. Confirm changes to an existing order (i.e. accept cancel and replace requests) 3. Relay order status information 4. Relay fill information on working orders 5. Relay fill information on tradeable or restricted tradeable quotes 6. Reject orders 7. Report post-trade fees calculations associated with a trade

message.name: OrderCancelReject
message.description: The order cancel reject message is issued by the broker upon receipt of a cancel request or cancel/replace request message which cannot be honored.

message.name: Logon
message.description: The logon message authenticates a user establishing a connection to a remote system.

message.name: News
message.description: The news message is a general free format message between the broker and institution.

message.name: Email
message.description: The email message is similar to the format and purpose of the News message, however, it is intended for private use between two parties.

message.name: NewOrderSingle
message.description: The new order message type is used by institutions wishing to electronically submit securities and forex orders to a broker for execution.

message.name: NewOrderList
message.description: The NewOrderList Message can be used in one of two ways depending on which market conventions are being followed.

message.name: OrderCancelRequest
message.description: The order cancel request message requests the cancellation of all of the remaining quantity of an existing order.

message.name: OrderCancelReplaceRequest
message.description: The order cancel/replace request is used to change the parameters of an existing order.

message.name: OrderStatusRequest
message.description: The order status request message is used by the institution to generate an order status message back from the broker.

message.name: Allocation
message.description: The Allocation message provides the ability to specify how an order or set of orders should be subdivided amongst one or more accounts.

message.name: ListCancelRequest
message.description: The list cancel request message type is used by institutions wishing to cancel previously submitted lists either before or during execution.

message.name: ListExecute
message.description: The list execute message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to begin execution of a previously submitted list.

message.name: ListStatusRequest
message.description: The list status request message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to generate status messages for a list.

message.name: ListStatus
message.description: The list status message is issued as the response to a List Status Request message sent in an unsolicited fashion by the sell-side.

message.name: AllocationAck
message.description: The Allocation ACK message is used to acknowledge the receipt and status of an Allocation message.

message.name: DontKnowTrade
message.description: The Don’t Know Trade (DK) message notifies a trading partner that an electronically received execution has been rejected. This message can be thought of as an execution reject message.

message.name: QuoteRequest
message.description: In some markets it is the practice to request quotes from brokers prior to placement of an order. The quote request message is used for this purpose. This message is commonly referred to as an Request For Quote (RFQ)

message.name: Quote
message.description: The quote message is used as the response to a Quote Request message in both indicative, tradeable, and restricted tradeable quoting markets.

message.name: SettlementInstructions
message.description: The Settlement Instructions message provides the broker’s, the institution’s, or the intermediary’s instructions for trade settlement.

message.name: MarketDataRequest
message.description: Some systems allow the transmission of real-time quote, order, trade and/or other price information on a subscription basis. A Market Data Request is a general request for market data on specific securities or forex quotes.

message.name: MarketDataSnapshotFullRefresh
message.description: The Market Data messages are used as the response to a Market Data Request message.

message.name: MarketDataIncrementalRefresh
message.description: The second Market Data message format is used for incremental updates.

message.name: MarketDataRequestReject
message.description: The Market Data Request Reject is used when the broker cannot honor the Market Data Request, due to business or technical reasons.

message.name: QuoteCancel
message.description: The Quote Cancel message is used by an originator of quotes to cancel quotes.

message.name: QuoteStatusRequest
message.description: The quote status request message is used for the following purposes in markets that employ tradeable or restricted tradeable quotes: * For the issuer of a quote in a market to query the status of that quote (using the QuoteID to specify the target quote). * To subscribe and unsubscribe for Quote Status Report messages for one or more securities.

message.name: MassQuoteAcknowledgement
message.description: Mass Quote Acknowledgement is used as the application level response to a Mass Quote message.

message.name: SecurityDefinitionRequest
message.description: The Security Definition Request message is used for the following: 1. Request a specific Security to be traded with the second party. The request security can be defined as a multileg security made up of one or more instrument legs.

message.name: SecurityDefinition
message.description: The Security Definition message is used for the following: 1. Accept the security defined in a Security Definition message. 2. Accept the security defined in a Security Definition message with changes to the definition and/or identity of the security. 3. Reject the security requested in a Security Definition message

message.name: SecurityStatusRequest
message.description: The Security Status Request message provides for the ability to request the status of a security.

message.name: SecurityStatus
message.description: The Security Status message provides for the ability to report changes in status to a security.

message.name: TradingSessionStatusRequest
message.description: The Trading Session Status Request is used to request information on the status of a market.

message.name: TradingSessionStatus
message.description: The Trading Session Status provides information on the status of a market.

message.name: MassQuote
message.description: The Mass Quote message can contain quotes for multiple securities to support applications that allow for the mass quoting of an option series.

message.name: BidRequest
message.description: The BidRequest Message can be used in one of two ways depending on which market conventions are being followed.

message.name: BidResponse
message.description: The Bid Response message can be used in one of two ways depending on which market conventions are being followed. In the "Non disclosed" convention the Bid Response message can be used to supply a bid based on the sector, country, index and liquidity information contained within the corresponding bid request message. See "Program/Basket/List Trading" for an example. In the "Disclosed" convention the Bid Response message can be used to supply bids based on the List Order Detail messages sent in advance of the corresponding Bid Request message.

message.name: ListStrikePrice
message.description: The strike price message is used to exchange strike price information for principal trades.

message.name: RegistrationInstructions
message.description: The Registration Instructions message type may be used by institutions or retail intermediaries wishing to electronically submit registration information to a broker or fund manager (for CIV) for an order or for an allocation.

message.name: RegistrationInstructionsResponse
message.description: The Registration Instructions Response message type may be used by broker or fund manager (for CIV) in response to a Registration Instructions message submitted by an institution or retail intermediary for an order or for an allocation.

message.name: OrderMassCancelRequest
message.description: The order mass cancel request message requests the cancellation of all of the remaining quantity of a group of orders matching criteria specified within the request.

message.name: OrderMassCancelReport
message.description: The Order Mass Cancel Report is used to acknowledge an Order Mass Cancel Request.

message.name: NewOrderCross
message.description: Used to submit a cross order into a market.

message.name: CrossOrderCancelReplaceRequest
message.description: Used to modify a cross order previously submitted using the New Order - Cross message.

message.name: CrossOrderCancelRequest
message.description: Used to fully cancel the remaining open quantity of a cross order.

message.name: SecurityTypeRequest
message.description: The Security Type Request message is used to return a list of security types available from a counterparty or market.

message.name: SecurityTypes
message.description: The Security Type message is used to return a list of security types available from a counterparty or market.

message.name: SecurityListRequest
message.description: The Security List Request message is used to return a list of securities from the counterparty that match criteria provided on the request

message.name: SecurityList
message.description: The Security List message is used to return a list of securities that matches the criteria specified in a Security List Request.

message.name: DerivativeSecurityListRequest
message.description: The Derivative Security List Request message is used to return a list of securities from the counterparty that match criteria provided on the request

message.name: DerivativeSecurityList
message.description: The Derivative Security List message is used to return a list of securities that matches the criteria specified in a Derivative Security List Request.

message.name: NewOrderMultileg
message.description: The New Order - Multileg is provided to submit orders for securities that are made up of multiple securities, known as legs.

message.name: MultilegOrderCancelReplaceRequest
message.description: Used to modify a multileg order previously submitted using the New Order - Multileg message.

message.name: TradeCaptureReportRequest
message.description: The Trade Capture Report can be used to: • Request one or more trade capture reports based upon selection criteria provided on the trade capture report request • Subscribe for trade capture reports based upon selection criteria provided on the trade capture report request.

message.name: TradeCaptureReport
message.description: The Trade Capture Report message can be: • Used to report trades between counterparties. • Can be sent unsolicited between counterparties. • Sent as a reply to a Trade Capture Report Request. • Can be used to report unmatched and matched trades.

message.name: OrderMassStatusRequest
message.description: The order mass status request message requests the status for orders matching criteria specified within the request.

message.name: QuoteRequestReject
message.description: The Quote Request Reject message is used to reject Quote Request messages for all quoting models.

message.name: RFQRequest
message.description: In tradeable and restricted tradeable quoting markets – Quote Requests are issued by counterparties interested in ascertaining the market for an instrument.

message.name: QuoteStatusReport
message.description: The quote status report message is used: • As the response to a Quote Status Request message • As a response to a Quote Cancel message

component.name: CommissionData
component.description: The CommissionDate component block is used to carry commission information such as the type of commission and the rate.

component.name: Instrument
component.description: The Instrument component block contains all the fields commonly used to describe a security or instrument. Typically the data elements in this component block are considered the static data of a security, data that may be commonly found in a security master database. The Instrument component block can be used to describe any asset type supported by FIX.

component.name: InstrumentLeg
component.description: The InstrumentLeg component block, like the Instrument component block, contains all the fields commonly used to describe a security or instrument. In the case of the InstrumentLeg component block it describes a security used in multileg-oriented messages. Refer to the Instrument component block comments as this component block mirrors Instrument, except for the noted fields. Several multileg-oriented messages specify an Instrument Leg component block. An instrument can have zero or more instrument legs. The fundamental business rule that applies to the multileg instrument is that the multileg instrument is defined as the combination of instrument legs. The multileg instrument must be able to be traded atomically – that all instrument legs are traded or none are traded. The LegRatioQty[623] is used to define the quantity of the leg that makes up a single unit of the multleg instrument. An option butterfly strategy is made up of three option legs.

component.name: NestedParties
component.description: The NestedParties component block is identical to the Parties Block. It is used in other component blocks and repeating groups when nesting will take place resulting in multiple occurrences of the Parties block within a single FIX message.. Use of NestedParties under these conditions avoids multiple references to the Parties block within the same message which is not allowed in FIX tag/value syntax.

component.name: OrderQtyData
component.description: The OrderQtyData component block contains the fields commonly used for indicating the amount or quantity of an order. Note that when this component block is marked as "required" in a message either one of these three fields must be used to identify the amount: OrderQty, CashOrderQty or OrderPercent (in the case of CIV).

component.name: Parties
component.description: The Parties component block is used to identify and convey information on the entities both central and peripheral to the financial transaction represented by the FIX message containing the Parties Block. The Parties block allows many different types of entites to be expressed through use of the PartyRole field and identifies the source of the PartyID through the the PartyIDSource.

component.name: SpreadOrBenchmarkCurveData
component.description: The SpreadOrBenchmarkCurveData component block is primarily used for Fixed Income to convey spread to a benchmark security or curve.

component.name: Stipulations
component.description: The Stipulations component block is used in Fixed Income to provide additional information on a given security. These additional information are usually not considered static data information.

component.name: UnderlyingInstrument
component.description: The UnderlyingInstrument component block, like the Instrument component block, contains all the fields commonly used to describe a security or instrument. In the case of the UnderlyingInstrument component block it describes an instrument which underlies the primary instrument Refer to the Instrument component block comments as this component block mirrors Instrument, except for the noted fields.

component.name: YieldData
component.description: The YieldData component block conveys yield information for a given Fixed Income security.

field.name: Account
field.description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

field.name: AdvId
field.description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: AdvRefID
field.description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: AdvSide
field.description: Broker's side of advertised trade

field.name: AdvTransType
field.description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

field.name: AvgPx
field.description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

field.name: BeginSeqNo
field.description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

field.name: BeginString
field.description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

field.name: BodyLength
field.description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

field.name: CheckSum
field.description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "Checksum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

field.name: ClOrdID
field.description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID or OnBehalfOfCompID as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

field.name: Commission
field.description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

field.name: CommType
field.description: Commission type

field.name: CumQty
field.description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: Currency
field.description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values.

field.name: EndSeqNo
field.description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

field.name: ExecID
field.description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) forExecType=I (Order Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: ExecInst
field.description: (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: ExecRefID
field.description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: HandlInst
field.description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

field.name: SecurityIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID value. Required if SecurityID is specified. Values 100+ are reserved for private security identifications

field.name: IOIid
field.description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: IOIQltyInd
field.description: Relative quality of indication

field.name: IOIRefID
field.description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: IOIQty
field.description: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

field.name: IOITransType
field.description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

field.name: LastCapacity
field.description: Broker capacity in order execution

field.name: LastMkt
field.description: Market of execution for last fill Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

field.name: LastPx
field.description: Price of this (last) fill.

field.name: LastQty
field.description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: LinesOfText
field.description: Identifies number of lines of text body

field.name: MsgSeqNum
field.description: Integer message sequence number.

field.name: MsgType
field.description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U1, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver.

field.name: NewSeqNo
field.description: New sequence number

field.name: OrderID
field.description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

field.name: OrderQty
field.description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or based on normal convention the number of contracts for options, futures, convertible bonds, etc. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: OrdStatus
field.description: Identifies current status of order. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: OrdType
field.description: Order type. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN DEPRECATED - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: OrigClOrdID
field.description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

field.name: OrigTime
field.description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

field.name: PossDupFlag
field.description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

field.name: Price
field.description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

field.name: RefSeqNum
field.description: Reference message sequence number

field.name: Rule80A
field.description: *** DEPRECATED FIELD - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** Note that the name of this field is changing to "OrderCapacity" as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. See the "Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market" appendix for market-specific usage of this field.

field.name: SecurityID
field.description: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource.

field.name: SenderCompID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

field.name: SenderSubID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

field.name: SendingTime
field.description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: Quantity
field.description: Overall/total quantity (e.g. number of shares) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: Side
field.description: Side of order

field.name: Symbol
field.description: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles)

field.name: TargetCompID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

field.name: TargetSubID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

field.name: Text
field.description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

field.name: TimeInForce
field.description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders. (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: TransactTime
field.description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: Urgency
field.description: Urgency flag

field.name: ValidUntilTime
field.description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: SettlmntTyp
field.description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, FutSettDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlmntTyp (63) and FutSettDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlmntTyp (63) is 0 (Regular) Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution.

field.name: FutSettDate
field.description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. If present, this field overrides SettlmntTyp (63). This field is required if the value of SettlmntTyp (63) is 6 (Future) or 8 (Sellers Option). This field must be omitted if the value of SettlmntTyp (63) is 7 (When and If Issued) (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

field.name: SymbolSfx
field.description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167). Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory

field.name: ListID
field.description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

field.name: ListSeqNo
field.description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

field.name: TotNoOrders
field.description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

field.name: ListExecInst
field.description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

field.name: AllocID
field.description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: AllocTransType
field.description: Identifies allocation transaction type *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

field.name: RefAllocID
field.description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType=Replace or Cancel or with AllocType = "Sellside Calculated Using Preliminary". (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

field.name: NoOrders
field.description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

field.name: AvgPrxPrecision
field.description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

field.name: TradeDate
field.description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

field.name: PositionEffect
field.description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

field.name: NoAllocs
field.description: Number of repeating AllocAccount/AllocPrice entries.

field.name: AllocAccount
field.description: Sub-account mnemonic

field.name: AllocQty
field.description: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: ProcessCode
field.description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount / AllocPrice/AllocQty / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

field.name: NoRpts
field.description: Total number of reports within series.

field.name: RptSeq
field.description: Sequence number of message within report series.

field.name: CxlQty
field.description: Total quantity canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: AllocStatus
field.description: Identifies status of allocation.

field.name: AllocRejCode
field.description: Identifies reason for rejection.

field.name: Signature
field.description: Electronic signature

field.name: SecureDataLen
field.description: Length of encrypted message

field.name: SecureData
field.description: Actual encrypted data stream

field.name: SignatureLength
field.description: Number of bytes in signature field.

field.name: EmailType
field.description: Email message type.

field.name: RawDataLength
field.description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

field.name: RawData
field.description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

field.name: PossResend
field.description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

field.name: EncryptMethod
field.description: Method of encryption.

field.name: StopPx
field.description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

field.name: ExDestination
field.description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

field.name: CxlRejReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

field.name: OrdRejReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

field.name: IOIQualifier
field.description: Code to qualify IOI use.

field.name: Issuer
field.description: Company name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines) see also Volume 7: "PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME - Euro Soverign Issuer Codes"

field.name: SecurityDesc
field.description: Security description.

field.name: HeartBtInt
field.description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

field.name: MinQty
field.description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: MaxFloor
field.description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

field.name: TestReqID
field.description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

field.name: ReportToExch
field.description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

field.name: LocateReqd
field.description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

field.name: OnBehalfOfCompID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

field.name: OnBehalfOfSubID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

field.name: QuoteID
field.description: Unique identifier for quote

field.name: NetMoney
field.description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

field.name: SettlCurrAmt
field.description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

field.name: SettlCurrency
field.description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

field.name: ForexReq
field.description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

field.name: OrigSendingTime
field.description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

field.name: GapFillFlag
field.description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

field.name: NoExecs
field.description: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

field.name: ExpireTime
field.description: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: DKReason
field.description: Reason for execution rejection.

field.name: DeliverToCompID

field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedIssuer field.

field.name: EncodedIssuer
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Issuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Issuer field.

field.name: EncodedSecurityDescLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityDesc field.

field.name: EncodedSecurityDesc
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityDesc field.

field.name: EncodedListExecInstLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst field.

field.name: EncodedListExecInst
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst field.

field.name: EncodedTextLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText field.

field.name: EncodedText
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

field.name: EncodedSubjectLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject field.

field.name: EncodedSubject
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

field.name: EncodedHeadlineLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline field.

field.name: EncodedHeadline
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

field.name: EncodedAllocTextLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText field.

field.name: EncodedAllocText
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

field.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer field.

field.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

field.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc field.

field.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

field.name: AllocPrice
field.description: Executed price for an AllocAccount entry used when using "executed price" vs. "average price" allocations (e.g. Japan).

field.name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
field.description: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: QuoteEntryRejectReason
field.description: Reason Quote Entry was rejected:

field.name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
field.description: The last MsgSeqNum value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

field.name: OnBehalfOfSendingTime
field.description: *** DEPRECATED FIELD - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** Used when a message is sent via a "hub" or "service bureau". If A sends to Q (the hub) who then sends to B via a separate FIX session, then when Q sends to B the value of this field should represent the SendingTime on the message A sent to Q. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: RefTagID
field.description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

field.name: RefMsgType
field.description: The MsgType of the FIX message being referenced.

field.name: SessionRejectReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message.

field.name: BidRequestTransType
field.description: Identifies the Bid Request message type.

field.name: ContraBroker
field.description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

field.name: ComplianceID
field.description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

field.name: SolicitedFlag
field.description: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

field.name: ExecRestatementReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for an ExecutionRpt message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

field.name: BusinessRejectRefID
field.description: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

field.name: BusinessRejectReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.

field.name: GrossTradeAmt
field.description: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty * AvgPx) expressed in units of currency.

field.name: NoContraBrokers
field.description: The number of ContraBroker entries.

field.name: MaxMessageSize
field.description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

field.name: NoMsgTypes
field.description: Number of MsgTypes in repeating group.

field.name: MsgDirection
field.description: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

field.name: NoTradingSessions
field.description: Number of TradingSessionIDs in repeating group.

field.name: TotalVolumeTraded
field.description: Total volume (quantity) traded.

field.name: DiscretionInst
field.description: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffset is related to and should be mathematically added to.

field.name: DiscretionOffset
field.description: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst.

field.name: BidID
field.description: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

field.name: ClientBidID
field.description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

field.name: ListName
field.description: Descriptive name for list order.

field.name: TotalNumSecurities
field.description: Total number of securities.

field.name: BidType
field.description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request.

field.name: NumTickets
field.description: Total number of tickets.

field.name: SideValue1
field.description: Amounts in currency

field.name: SideValue2
field.description: Amounts in currency

field.name: NoBidDescriptors
field.description: Number of BidDescriptor entries.

field.name: BidDescriptorType
field.description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor.

field.name: BidDescriptor
field.description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorType. If BidDescriptorType =1 Industrials etc - Free text If BidDescriptorType =2 "FR" etc - ISO Country Codes If BidDescriptorType =3 FT100, FT250, STOX - Free text

field.name: SideValueInd
field.description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

field.name: LiquidityPctLow
field.description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: LiquidityPctHigh
field.description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: LiquidityValue
field.description: Value between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency

field.name: EFPTrackingError
field.description: Eg Used in EFP trades 12% (EFP – Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

field.name: FairValue
field.description: Used in EFP trades

field.name: OutsideIndexPct
field.description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ValueOfFutures
field.description: Used in EFP trades

field.name: LiquidityIndType
field.description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

field.name: WtAverageLiquidity
field.description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ExchangeForPhysical
field.description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

field.name: OutMainCntryUIndex
field.description: Value of stocks in Currency

field.name: CrossPercent
field.description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ProgRptReqs
field.description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

field.name: ProgPeriodInterval
field.description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don’t send status.

field.name: IncTaxInd
field.description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

field.name: NumBidders
field.description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

field.name: TradeType
field.description: Code to represent the type of trade.

field.name: BasisPxType
field.description: Code to represent the basis price type.

field.name: NoBidComponents
field.description: Indicates the number of list entries.

field.name: Country
field.description: ISO Country Code in field

field.name: TotNoStrikes
field.description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation.

field.name: PriceType
field.description: Code to represent the price type.

field.name: DayOrderQty
field.description: For GT orders, the OrderQty less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty = OrderQty – (CumQty - DayCumQty)

field.name: DayCumQty
field.description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

field.name: DayAvgPx
field.description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

field.name: GTBookingInst
field.description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

field.name: NoStrikes
field.description: Number of list strike price entries.

field.name: ListStatusType
field.description: Code to represent the status type.

field.name: NetGrossInd
field.description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

field.name: ListOrderStatus
field.description: Code to represent the status of a list order.

field.name: ExpireDate
field.description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market’s business practices

field.name: ListExecInstType
field.description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst.

field.name: CxlRejResponseTo
field.description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to.

field.name: UnderlyingCouponRate
field.description: Underlying security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

field.name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
field.description: Underlying security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

field.name: ContraTradeQty
field.description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker.

field.name: ContraTradeTime
field.description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: LiquidityNumSecurities
field.description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency.

field.name: MultiLegReportingType
field.description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securiteis, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

field.name: StrikeTime
field.description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

field.name: ListStatusText
field.description: Free format text string related to List Status.

field.name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText field.

field.name: EncodedListStatusText
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

field.name: PartyIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole specified. See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block" Valid values: Applicable to all PartyRoles unless otherwise specified: B = BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code (ISO 9362 - See "Appendix 6-B") C = Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D = Proprietary/Custom code E = ISO Country Code F = Settlement Entity Location (note if Local Market Settlement use "E = ISO Country Code") (see "Appendix 6-G" for valid values) For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for Equities: 1 = Korean Investor ID 2 = Taiwanese Qualified Foreign Investor ID QFII / FID 3 = Taiwanese Trading Account 4 = Malaysian Central Depository (MCD) number 5 = Chinese B Share (Shezhen and Shanghai) See Volume 4: "Example Usage of PartyRole="Investor ID" " For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for CIV: 6 = UK National Insurance or Pension Number 7 = US Social Security Number 8 = US Employer Identification Number 9 = Australian Business Number A = Australian Tax File Number

field.name: PartyID
field.description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

field.name: TotalVolumeTradedDate
field.description: Date of TotalVolumeTraded.

field.name: TotalVolumeTradedTime
field.description: Time of TotalVolumeTraded.

field.name: NetChgPrevDay
field.description: Net change from previous day’s closing price vs. last traded price.

field.name: PartyRole
field.description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID specified. See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

field.name: NoPartyIDs
field.description: Number of PartyID, PartyIDSource, and PartyRole entries

field.name: NoSecurityAltID
field.description: Number of SecurityAltID entries.

field.name: SecurityAltID
field.description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

field.name: SecurityAltIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource field

field.name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
field.description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID entries.

field.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
field.description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

field.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

field.name: Product
field.description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

field.name: CFICode
field.description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

field.name: UnderlyingProduct
field.description: Underlying security’s Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

field.name: UnderlyingCFICode
field.description: Underlying security’s CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461)field

field.name: TestMessageIndicator
field.description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

field.name: QuantityType
field.description: Designates the type of quantities (e.g. OrderQty) specified. Used for MBS and TIPS Fixed Income security types.

field.name: BookingRefID
field.description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

field.name: IndividualAllocID
field.description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

field.name: RoundingDirection
field.description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV – indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where OrderCashAmt or (for CIV only) OrderPercent are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus was 10 – "round down" would give 320 units, "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

field.name: RoundingModulus
field.description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 10 means round to a multiple of 10 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

field.name: CountryOfIssue
field.description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

field.name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
field.description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

field.name: LocaleOfIssue
field.description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org. See "Volume 7 – PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME" for example.

field.name: NoRegistDtls
field.description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

field.name: MailingDtls
field.description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

field.name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
field.description: The ISO 3166 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

field.name: PaymentRef
field.description: "Settlement Payment Reference" – A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

field.name: DistribPaymentMethod
field.description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Direct Credit (BECS, BACS) 9 = ACH Credit 10 = BPAY 11 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 12 = Reinvest in fund 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: CashDistribCurr
field.description: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions– see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: CommCurrency
field.description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: CancellationRights
field.description: For CIV – A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

field.name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
field.description: For CIV - A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

field.name: MailingInst
field.description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

field.name: TransBkdTime
field.description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

field.name: ExecPriceType
field.description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

field.name: ExecPriceAdjustment
field.description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType

field.name: DateOfBirth
field.description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

field.name: TradeReportTransType
field.description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type

field.name: CardHolderName
field.description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardNumber
field.description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardExpDate
field.description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardIssNo
field.description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

field.name: PaymentMethod
field.description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Debit Card 9 = Direct Debit (BECS) 10 = Direct Credit (BECS) 11 = Credit Card 12 = ACH Debit 13 = ACH Credit 14 = BPAY 15 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: RegistAcctType
field.description: For CIV – a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager’s account types is required.

field.name: Designation
field.description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker’s nominee or street name.

field.name: TaxAdvantageType
field.description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 0=None/Not Applicable (default) 1 = Maxi ISA (UK) 2 = TESSA (UK) 3 = Mini Cash ISA (UK) 4 = Mini Stocks and Shares ISA (UK) 5 = Mini Insurance ISA (UK) 6 = Current year payment (US) 7 = Prior year payment (US) 8 = Asset transfer (US) 9 = Employee - prior year (US) 10 = Employee – current year (US) 11 = Employer - prior year (US) 12 = Employer – current year (US) 13 = Non-fund prototype IRA (US) 14 = Non-fund qualified plan (US) 15 = Defined contribution plan (US) 16 = Individual Retirement Account (US) 17 = Individual Retirement Account – Rollover (US) 18 = KEOGH (US) 19 = Profit Sharing Plan (US) 20 = 401K (US) 21 = Self-Directed IRA (US) 22 = 403(b) (US) 23 = 457 (US) 24 = Roth IRA (fund prototype) (US) 25 = Roth IRA (non-prototype) (US) 26 = Roth Conversion IRA (fund prototype) (US) 27 = Roth Conversion IRA (non-prototype) (US) 28 = Education IRA (fund prototype) (US) 29 = Education IRA (non-prototype) (US) 30 – 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: RegistRejReasonText
field.description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

field.name: FundRenewWaiv
field.description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

field.name: CashDistribAgentName
field.description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

field.name: CashDistribAgentCode
field.description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

field.name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
field.description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

field.name: CashDistribPayRef
field.description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

field.name: CardStartDate
field.description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: PaymentDate
field.description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

field.name: PaymentRemitterID
field.description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

field.name: RegistStatus
field.description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager

field.name: RegistRejReasonCode
field.description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field.

field.name: RegistRefID
field.description: Reference identifier for the RegistID with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType transaction types.

field.name: RegistDetls
field.description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

field.name: NoDistribInsts
field.description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

field.name: RegistEmail
field.description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

field.name: DistribPercentage
field.description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

field.name: RegistID
field.description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

field.name: RegistTransType
field.description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel

field.name: ExecValuationPoint
field.description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

field.name: OrderPercent
field.description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor’s total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor’s cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty in shares/units for subsequent messages.

field.name: OwnershipType
field.description: The relationship between Registration parties.

field.name: NoContAmts
field.description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

field.name: ContAmtType
field.description: Type of Contract Amount. For UK valid values include: 1 = Commission Amount (actual) 2 = Commission % (actual) 3 = Initial Charge Amount 4 = Initial Charge % 5 = Discount Amount 6 = Discount % 7 = Dilution Levy Amount 8 = Dilution Levy % 9 = Exit Charge Amount 10 = Exit Charge % 11 = Fund-based Renewal Commission % (a.k.a. Trail commission) 12 = Projected Fund Value (i.e. for investments intended to realise or exceed a specific future value) 13 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Order value) 14 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Projected Fund value) 15 = Net Settlement Amount NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 12/13.

field.name: ContAmtValue
field.description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType.

field.name: ContAmtCurr
field.description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix A; Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: OwnerType
field.description: Identifies the type of owner.

field.name: PartySubID
field.description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID, PartyIDSource, and PartyRole.

field.name: NestedPartyID
field.description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

field.name: NestedPartyIDSource
field.description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

field.name: SecondaryClOrdID
field.description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID used by an exchange or executing system.

field.name: SecondaryExecID
field.description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID used by an exchange or executing system.

field.name: OrderCapacity
field.description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions field)

field.name: OrderRestrictions
field.description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

field.name: MassCancelRequestType
field.description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request.

field.name: MassCancelResponse
field.description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

field.name: MassCancelRejectReason
field.description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

field.name: TotalAffectedOrders
field.description: Total number of orders affected by mass cancel request.

field.name: NoAffectedOrders
field.description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

field.name: AffectedOrderID
field.description: OrderID of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

field.name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
field.description: SecondaryOrderID of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

field.name: QuoteType

True Yield The yield calculated with coupon dates moved from a weekend or holiday to the next valid settlement date.
Previous Close Yield The yield of a bond based on the closing price 1 day ago.
Yield to Longest Average (Sinking Fund Bonds) The yield assuming only mandatory sinks are taken. This results in a slower paydown of debt; the yield is then calculated to the final payment date.
Yield to Longest Average Life The yield assuming only mandatory sinks are taken. This results in a lower paydown of debt; the yield is then calculated to the final payment date.
Yield to Maturity The yield of a bond to its maturity date.
Mark To Market Yield An adjustment in the valuation of a securities portfolio to reflect the current market values of the respective securities in the portfolio.
Open Average Yield The average yield of the respective securities in the portfolio.
Yield to Next Put The yield to the date at which the bond holder can next put the bond to the issuer.
Proceeds Yield The CD equivalent yield when the remaining time to maturity is less than two years.
Semi-annual Yield The yield of a bond whose coupon payments are reinvested semi-annually
Yield to Shortest Average Life same as AVGLIFE above.

Yield to Shortest Average (Sinking Fund Bonds) The yield assuming that all sinks (mandatory and voluntary) are taken. This results in a faster paydown of debt; the yield is then calculated to the final payment date.
Simple Yield The yield of a bond assuming no reinvestment of coupon payments. (Act/360 day count)
Yield to Tender Date The yield on a Municipal bond to its mandatory tender date.
Yield Value Of 1/32 The amount that the yield will change for a 1/32nd change in price.
Yield To Worst Convention The lowest yield to all possible redemption date scenarios.
Tax Equivalent Yield The after tax yield grossed up by the maximum federal tax rate of 39.6%. For comparison to taxable yields.
Annual Yield The annual interest or dividend income an investment earns, expressed as a percentage of the investments total value.
Closing Yield Most Recent Year The yield of a bond based on the closing price as of the most recent years end.
Yield To Next Refund (Sinking Fund Bonds) Yield assuming all bonds are redeemed at the next refund date at the redemption price.

After Tax Yield (Municipals) The yield on the bond net of any tax consequences from holding the bond. The discount on municipal securities can be subject to both capital gains taxes and ordinary income taxes. Calculated from dollar price.
Yield At Issue (Municipals) The yield of the bond offered on the issue date.
Yield To Average Life The yield assuming that all sinks (mandatory and voluntary) are taken at par. This results in a faster paydown of debt; the yield is then calculated to the average life date.
Yield To Average Maturity The yield achieved by substituting a bond's average maturity for the issue's final maturity date.
Book Yield The yield of a security calculated by using its book value instead of the current market price. This term is typically used in the US domestic market.
Yield to Next Call The yield of a bond to the next possible call date.
Yield Change Since Close The change in the yield since the previous day's closing yield.
Compound Yield The yield of certain Japanese bonds based on its price. Certain Japanese bonds have irregular first or last coupons, and the yield is calculated compound for these irregular periods.
Current Yield Annual interest on a bond divided by the market value. The actual income rate of return as opposed to the coupon rate expressed as a percentage.
True Gross Yield Yield calculated using the price including accrued interest, where coupon dates are moved from holidays and weekends to the next trading day.
Government Equivalent Yield Ask yield based on semi-annual coupons compounding in all periods and actual/actual calendar.

Yield with Inflation Assumption Based on price, the return an investor would require on a normal bond that would make the real return equal to that of the inflation-indexed bond, assuming a constant inflation rate.
Inverse Floater Bond Yield Inverse floater semi-annual bond equivalent rate.
Closing Yield Most Recent Quarter The yield of a bond based on the closing price as of the most recent quarters end.
Most Recent Closing Yield The last available yield stored in history, computed using price.
Closing Yield Most Recent Month The yield of a bond based on the closing price as of the most recent month's end.
Closing Yield The yield of a bond based on the closing price.
